race.comment: CREEK (5) is busting to break through and gets a perfect chance returning from the city. The one he chased last time looks quite handy, and the runner-up Swiftie Harriet has since won in Victoria. Peaking now and is the one to beat. ANDREW'S MEMORY (4) never looked likely last time in town but warmed late. Better suited back at this level and is a genuine hope on best form. NOSIE BY NATURE (10) gave backers a great sight last time at Gawler, only to be gunned down late. Back on track and can give this a shake. LASTAR (9) doesn't win out of turn but has claims on best efforts and gets in light with the 3kg claimer engaged. One to keep safe in the minors.
